OL,6,FShe received a 20-month prison
OL,7,Fsentence, suspended for 18 months, and
OL,8,Fwill have to complete 10
OL,9,Frehabilitation days and 100 hours'
OL,10,Funpaid work.
OL,12,FIn a victim impact statement read to
OL,13,Fthe court, Mrs Clark described how
OL,14,FHolland had been a trusted member of
OL,15,Fthe household.
OL,17,F"She was more than a cleaner. She had
OL,18,Faccess to my bank cards, and I would
OL,19,Fhappily let her go into my purse. I
OL,20,Fbelieved her to be trustworthy.
