OL,6,F"The incident related to the loss of
OL,7,Firreplaceable, sentimental and
OL,8,Fpriceless pieces of jewellery."
OL,10,FMrs Clark said she was "extremely
OL,11,Fdistraught and upset" to discover that
OL,12,Fthe "irreplaceable, sentimental and
OL,13,Fpriceless" jewellery was missing.
OL,15,FShe later phoned Holland who denied
OL,16,Fany knowledge of the theft.
OL,18,FIn her statement, Clark also said
OL,19,FHolland had told her "how hard-up she
OL,20,Fwas" but was later able to buy several
OL,21,Fexpensive household white goods items.
